<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-84-0513 </DOCNO><TEXT>The potential of membrane separation for economic unmanned natural gasseparation is reviewed, and advances in polymer technology leading tothinner membranes, improved characteristics for gas transfer and morecompact manufacturing techniques in the form of hollow fibres are outlined.The principles of membrane operation, the compact modular designs, easeof operation, and potential recovery of carbon dioxide for use in enhancedoil recovery are discussed.</TEXT></DOC>